Mangal SINGH, Appellant, v. Edward L. HAFF, District Director of Immigration and Naturalization for the Port of San Francisco, Cal., Appellee. No. 9477. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 2, 1940. Joseph P. Fallon, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., and R. B. McMillan and L. R. I&ercado, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of San Francisco, Cal., (A. J. Phelan, U. S. Immigration and Naturalization Service, of San Francisco, Cal., on the brief), for appellee.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order is affirmed upon the authority of Channan Singh v. Haff, 309 U.S. 634, 60 S.Ct. 720, 84 L.Ed. -, decided April 1, 1940, by the United States Supreme Court.
